WorkItem.Description:
Hi Jon,

Long time listener, first time caller.... love the show!

On page 48 and in the finished code the following lines throw and error:

public ActionResult Browse(string genre)
{
    // Retrieve Genre and its Associated Albums from database
    var genreModel = storeDB.Genres.Include("Albums").Single(g => g.Name == genre);
    
    return View(genreModel);
}

The error message I get is:

"A specified Include path is not valid. The EntityType 'MvcMusicStore.Models.Genre' does not declare a navigation property with the name 'Albums'."

The URL's that causes the issue:

http://localhost:xyz/store/browse
http://localhost:xyz/store/browse?genre=Jazz

I found via google there are a few people that have come across this line, not sure of the fix though... :)

Cheers,
John

Comments.Message:
Hey, sorry you're hitting a problem. The first thing to check is if you missed the navigation property in your Genre class. Does it look like this?

using System.Collections.Generic; 

namespace MvcMusicStore.Models 
{ 
    public partial class Genre 
    { 
        public int      GenreId     { get; set; } 
        public string   Name        { get; set; } 
        public string   Description { get; set; } 
        public List<Album> Albums   { get; set; } 
    } 
}

Note the Albums property at the end.

Also - make sure you're using the latest release of the Music Store tutorial.
